{"lemma":"صَيْفٌ","slug":"صَيْفٌ","root":"ص.#.ف","root_slug":"ص-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَيْف","root":"صيف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25365"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"summer","examples":[{"text":"إِيلَافِهِمْ رِحْلَةَ ٱلشِّتَاءِ وَٱلصَّيْفِ","english":"Their accustomed security in the caravan of winter and summer"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Perhaps a euphemism for قَيْظ (qayẓ) meaning “summer” in other West Semitic languages, from the root ص ف و (ṣ f w) “to be clear”."},"ipa":["/sˤajf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25365","headword_ar":"صَيْفٌ","root":"Syf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain portion of the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by ISk to be fem.: (TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='N","text_ar":"شِتَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; q. v.:) [but by others I find it treated as masc.:] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the seasons"},{"kind":"text","text":"is well known: (M:) Lth says, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the quarters of the year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is applied by the vulgar to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a half of the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half-year commencing at the vernal equinox;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the other half-year being called by them the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='","text_ar":"شِتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Az says, it is, with the Arabs, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"division which the vulgar in El-'Irák"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and Khurásán call the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it consists of three months;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the division that next follows it is with the Arabs the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamorap","text_ar":"جَمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyoZ","text_ar":"قِيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then, after this, is the division called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyf","text_ar":"خَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then, after this, the division called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$itaA='","text_ar":"شِتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [i. e.] it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter of the year vulgarly called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencing when the sun enters Aries:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but is applied by the vulgar to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter commencing when the sun enters Cancer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zmn","text_ar":"زمن"},{"kind":"text","text":"; q. v.:) [F says,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayoZ","text_ar":"قَيْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot season"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and [Sgh says,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the divisions of the year; which is after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) [but unless this explanation in the O denote only a vulgar meaning, and the latter of the two explanations in the K be virtually a repetition, we must suppose that, in each of them, by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant the season of rain thus termed, which ends in March: (see the latter of the two tables which I have inserted voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamanN","text_ar":"زَمَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) most probably, I think, both have been faultily transcribed from what here follows; for the S is largely copied in the O, and the S and O are among the principal sources of the K, which generally follows the O when it differs (rightly or wrongly) from the S:] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the divisions of the year; which is after"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abiyEu AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"الرَّبِيعُ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and before"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqayoZu","text_ar":"القَيْظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [this admits of two renderings, both of which are correct; namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter after the season of two months called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrbyE AlAw~l","text_ar":"الربيع الاوّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which ends in March"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and before the quarter called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqyZ","text_ar":"القيظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is summer"},{"kind":"text","text":"); and also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season of two months after that called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrbyE AlAw~l","text_ar":"الربيع الاوّل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and before the similar season called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqyZ","text_ar":"القيظ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (see the former of the two tables to which I have referred above:) but probably the latter only was meant by him who first gave. this explanation:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoyaAfN","text_ar":"اَصْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuyuwfN","text_ar":"صُيُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayofapN","text_ar":"صَيْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a more particular term [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see 2;)]; it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atowapN","text_ar":"شَتْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (O, K;) and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiyafN","text_ar":"صِيَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidarN","text_ar":"بِدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badorapN","text_ar":"بَدْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, O, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ayofa Day~aEoti","text_ar":"الصَّيْفَ ضَيَّعْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~abana","text_ar":"اللَّبَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a saying expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DyE","text_ar":"ضيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (O, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ayofu","text_ar":"الصَّيْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain that comes in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayof","text_ar":"صَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) [see, again, the second of the tables to which I have referred above, and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawoN","text_ar":"نَوٌْ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and (O, K) so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ay~ifu","text_ar":"الصَّيِّفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, O, K;) also signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the herbage thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or, (K,) accord. to Lth, (O,) the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rain that falls after the division"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a mistake for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) and so the former; (K;) and it is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ayofiY~u","text_ar":"الصَّيْفِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) which likewise signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the herbage thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence the prov., relating to the completing of the performance of a needful affair,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAmu Alr~abiyEi AlS~ayofu","text_ar":"تَمَامُ الرَّبِيعِ الصَّيْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The completion of"},{"kind":"text","text":"the rain called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is"},{"kind":"text","text":"that called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syf","text_ar":"صيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for the rain called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbyE","text_ar":"ربيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the first rain, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syf","text_ar":"صيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which is [next] after it. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yapu AlS~ayofi","text_ar":"ا=يَةُ الصَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the end"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=xir","text_ar":"ا=خِر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapu Aln~isaA='i","text_ar":"سُورَةُ النِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"4"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"th chapter of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but which verse I know not], mentioned in a tradition. (TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwm","text_ar":"بُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owl"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kr, M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K","O","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}